  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Suppose $n\\equiv 1\\pmod{m}$. We say that an edge-colouring of $K_n$ using $m$ colours is balanced if every vertex sees exactly $\\lfloor n/m\\rfloor$ many edges of each colours. \n\nFor which graphs $G$ is it true that, if $m=e(G)$, for all large $n\\equiv 1\\pmod{m}$, every balanced edge-colouring of $K_n$ with $m$ colours contains a rainbow copy of $G$? (That is, a subgraph isomorphic to $G$ where each edge receives a different colour.)",
